name: Standing Single Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and your hands on your hips. | Step:2 Shift your weight onto your left leg and lift your right foot off the ground, bending your knee. | Step:3 Slowly curl your right heel towards your glutes, squeezing your hamstring. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your right foot back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Concentration Curl (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing up and your arm extended down towards the floor. | Step:3 Rest your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder while contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms and repeat.

name: Bench Hip Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back against the bench and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands on the bench for support. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and hamstrings, then lift your hips off the bench until your body forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pull-In (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Start by sitting on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Place your hands on the sides of the stability ball for support. | Step:3 Engage your abs and slowly roll your hips forward, bringing your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly extend your legs back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Curl-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Side Lying Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs extended and your head supported by your arm. | Step:2 Hold your upper arm against your side and bend your elbow to curl your forearm towards your shoulder. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your forearm back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Triceps Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your upper arms close to your sides. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Biceps Leg Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your legs spread apart and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand and place your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:3 With your palm facing up, curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder while keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the edge of a step or platform with your heels hanging off and your toes on the step. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand and place your other hand on a wall or railing for support. | Step:3 Raise your heel as high as possible, lifting your body up onto your toes. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down below the step. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Weighted Seated Bicep Curl (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a medicine ball with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and let your arms hang down by your sides. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the medicine ball up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the medicine ball back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Biceps Curl (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbells while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Zottman Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Place your upper arms against the preacher bench and keep your elbows slightly bent. | Step:3 Curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders while keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:4 At the top of the movement, rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing downward. | Step:5 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, rotating your wrists back to the starting position as well. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Reverse Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:3 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:4 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Preacher Curl Over Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip, resting your elbow on the exercise ball. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Concentration Extension (On Knee)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with your right hand and place your elbow on the inside of your right knee. | Step:3 Extend your arm fully, keeping your elbow stationary and close to your knee. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arm back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Incline Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keep your back against the bench and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 While keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Reverse Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an overhand grip, palm facing down. | Step:3 Rest your forearm on your thigh, with your wrist hanging off the edge. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell towards the ground by flexing your wrist. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly curl your wrist back up towards your body. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Cable Seated Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a cable machine with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Grasp the cable attachment with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the cable attachment towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the cable attachment back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Fly
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight up over your chest, with a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:3 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, lower your arms out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then reverse the movement and bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Grip Skullcrusher
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your head at the end of the bench. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with a reverse grip, palms facing towards your face, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight up over your chest, keeping your elbows in and your wrists straight. | Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell towards your forehead by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope Hammer Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope attachment to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with a neutral grip (palms facing each other). | Step:4 Position your upper arms against the preacher bench pad, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:5 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the rope towards your shoulders by contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly lower the rope back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing One Arm Reverse Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your arm fully extended and close to your body, with your palm facing down. | Step:3 Slowly curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Triceps Extension (On Bench)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand and place your other hand on the bench for support. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbell overhead, keeping your upper arm close to your head and your elbow pointing forward. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbow, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:5 Extend your arm back up to the starting position, fully straightening your elbow. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Hammer Curl V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and rotate the palms of your hands until they are facing forward. | Step:3 This will be your starting position. | Step:4 Now, keeping the upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:6 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:7 Then, inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm French Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing up and your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight up towards the ceiling, keeping your elbow stationary. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Standing Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand, with your arm fully extended and palm facing inwards. | Step:2 Place your opposite hand on your thigh for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Pronated Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your back and head supported, and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing down, and extend your arm straight up above your shoulder. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbow. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then extend your arm back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Seated Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Place the balls of your feet on a raised surface such as a step or block, with your heels hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Hold onto the dumbbell for stability. | Step:4 Raise your heels as high as possible, lifting your body weight onto the balls of your feet. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the preacher curl pad is at chest height. | Step:2 Sit on the preacher curl bench and place your upper arms on the pad, gripping the cable attachment with an underhand grip. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your elbows tucked in at your sides. | Step:4 Slowly curl the cable attachment up towards your shoulders, squeezing your biceps at the top of the movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the cable attachment back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Two Arm Tricep Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle in each hand with your palms facing inwards and your arms bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, extend your forearms backwards until your arms are fully extended. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing One Arm Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbell overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:3 Keep your upper arm close to your head and perpendicular to the ground. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head, bending your elbow. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Revers Grip Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing down and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight back, squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Alternating Tricep Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight back, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the other arm, alternating sides with each repetition.

name: Lever Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and fully extend your arms in front of you. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the handles towards your forehead by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the handles back up to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your upper arms resting on the pad and your chest against the support. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbells as you contract your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to curl the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Good Morning
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and the barbell resting on your upper back. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge forward at the hips, pushing your buttocks back as if you were trying to touch the wall behind you with your glutes. | Step:3 Lower your torso until it is parallel to the ground, feeling a stretch in your hamstrings. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position by squeezing your glutes and pushing your hips forward. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Reverse One Arm Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grasp the cable handle with an underhand grip, palm facing down. | Step:3 Keep your elbow close to your side and slowly curl your forearm up towards your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your forearm back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Pushdown (With Rope Attachment)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope attachment to a high pulley on a cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and a slight bend in your knees. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Exhale and push the rope downward by extending your elbows until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then inhale and slowly return to the starting position by allowing your elbows to flex. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated One Arm Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a cable handle with one hand and place your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:3 Keep your upper arm stationary and curl the cable handle towards your shoulder while exhaling. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position while inhaling. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Drag Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grasp the cable attachment with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the cable attachment towards your shoulders by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the cable attachment back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Two Arm Curl On Incline Bench
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the cable handles with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the handles towards your shoulders while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the handles back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Hammer Curl On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbells while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the preacher curl pad is at chest height. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handle with an underhand grip and position your upper arm against the preacher curl pad. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Slowly curl the cable handle towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm against the pad. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:9 Switch arms and repeat the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Incline Curl V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Standing Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Alternate Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight up over your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:3 Lower one dumbbell down towards your head, bending at the elbow, while keeping the other arm extended. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then raise the dumbbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the other arm, alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Standing Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and exhale as you curl the weights up to shoulder level. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale as you slowly lower the weights back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell in front of you with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and your back straight throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Lift your shoulders up towards your ears as high as possible, squeezing your traps at the top. | Step:4 Hold for a moment, then slowly lower your shoulders back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and let the dumbbells hang by your sides. | Step:3 Raise your shoulders as high as possible, as if you are trying to touch your ears with your shoulders. | Step:4 Hold the contraction for a second, then slowly lower your shoulders back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Alternate Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Keep your upper arms stationary and exhale as you curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the barbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the barbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale as you slowly begin to lower the barbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, alternating arms.

name: Resistance Band Leg Extension
instructions: Step:1 Attach the resistance band to a sturdy anchor point and secure it around your ankle. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keeping your core engaged and your upper body stable, extend your leg straight out in front of you. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly return your leg to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Barbell Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your upper arms resting on the pad and your chest against the support. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an underhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the barbell up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Triceps Pushdown (V-Bar) (With Arm Blaster)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a v-bar attachment to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the v-bar with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Engage your triceps and exhale as you push the v-bar down until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your triceps. | Step:7 Inhale as you slowly return the v-bar to the starting position, maintaining control. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Leg Extension
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and backrest of the machine to fit your body. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet on the footpad. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or sidebars for stability. | Step:4 Extend your legs forward by straightening your knees, lifting the weight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the weight back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated Twist
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a cable machine with your feet flat on the ground and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands and extend your arms straight in front of you. | Step:3 Keeping your core engaged, slowly rotate your torso to one side, pulling the cable across your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the range of motion, then slowly rotate back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Standing Triceps Extension (With Towel)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a towel with both hands behind your head. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your ears and your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Slowly extend your forearms upward, squeezing your triceps at the top. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the towel back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Inner Biceps Curl V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and rotate the palms of your hands until they are facing forward. | Step:3 While holding your upper arms stationary, curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Slowly begin to bring the dumbbells back to the starting position as your breathe in. | Step:7 Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Wide Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing up and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Close Grip Behind Neck Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with a close grip behind your neck, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Keep your elbows close to your head and slowly lower the barbell towards the back of your head. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Neutral Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing the dumbbells to hang down. | Step:3 Keeping your wrists in a neutral position, curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Barbell Incline Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back against the pad and hold the ez barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:3 Extend your arms fully overhead, keeping your elbows close to your head. | Step:4 Lower the barbell behind your head by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing up. | Step:2 Rest your upper arms on the pad of the preacher bench, allowing your arms to fully extend. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell in your right hand as you contract your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to curl the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the movement with your left arm. | Step:7 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Prone Incline Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the bench to a 45-degree incline. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your chest and stomach resting against it. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing down and your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:6 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing One Arm Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with your right hand, palm facing down, and position your arm so that it is fully extended and parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Keep your elbow stationary and close to your body. | Step:4 Slowly bend your elbow, lowering the cable handle towards the back of your head. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then extend your arm back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and perform the exercise with your left arm.

name: Ez Barbell Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the ez barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary throughout the movement. | Step:3 Exhale as you curl the barbell up towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale as you slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Lying Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your head at the end of the bench. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart, and extend your arms straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the barbell towards your forehead by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Lying Triceps Extension Skull Crusher
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your head at the end of the bench. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart, and extend your arms straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the barbell towards your forehead by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment when the barbell is just above your forehead, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Reverse Grip Triceps Pushdown (Sz-Bar) (With Arm Blaster)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Engage your triceps and slowly push the bar down until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Overhead Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart, and raise it overhead. | Step:3 Lower the barbell behind your head by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms close to your head. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms to raise the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:2 Keep your upper arms stationary and exhale as you curl the barbell upward, contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the barbell is at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale as you slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Bar French Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball and hold an EZ barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight up, keeping your elbows close to your head. | Step:3 Slowly lower the barbell behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Kneeling Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a high pulley and kneel down facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Grasp the rope with a neutral grip (palms facing each other) and bring your hands to the sides of your head. | Step:3 Keep your elbows close to your head and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:4 Extend your forearms by contracting your triceps until your arms are fully extended. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position by bending your elbows. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline One Arm Fly
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on a decline bench with a dumbbell in one hand, resting it on your thigh. | Step:2 Using your thigh to help raise the dumbbell, lift it up to shoulder width with your palm facing your torso. | Step:3 Rotate your wrist so that the palm of your hand is facing forward. | Step:4 As you breathe in, lower the dumbbell slowly to the side until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:5 Exhale and use your chest muscles to bring the dumbbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Hammer Curl (With Rope)
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and a slight bend in your knees. | Step:2 Hold the cable rope attachment with an underhand grip, palms facing each other, and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the cable rope attachment until your biceps are fully contracted and the rope is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the cable rope attachment back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Machine Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the height of the smith machine bar to be at waist level. | Step:2 Stand facing the smith machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary. | Step:5 Exhale and curl the bar up towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly lower the bar back down to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell High Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Keep your upper arms stationary and curl the dumbbells as high as possible while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Bench Fly
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand, resting it on top of your thigh. | Step:2 Lie back on the bench, keeping the dumbbell pressed against your thigh. | Step:3 Using your free hand, help lift the dumbbell up to the starting position. | Step:4 Hold the dumbbell directly above your shoulder with your arm extended and palm facing inward. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbell out to the side in a wide arc, keeping a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:6 Pause when your arm is parallel to the ground, then reverse the movement and bring the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms and repeat.

name: Ez Barbell Close Grip Preacher Curl - Precision Variation
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher curl bench and place your upper arms on the pad, gripping the ez barbell with an underhand grip. | Step:2 Rest your triceps on the pad and fully extend your arms, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Slowly curl the barbell towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Lower the barbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Emphasize precision control.

name: Barbell Lying Triceps Extension Double
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your head at the end of the bench. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart, and extend your arms straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the barbell towards your forehead by bending your elbows. Focus on double movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Rotated Dumbbell Pronate-Grip Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands, palms facing down, and extend your arms straight up overhead. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms close to your head and elbows pointing forward, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Focus on rotated movement.

name: Dynamic Style Band Side Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the band with both hands, palms facing down. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out to the sides, keeping them parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Slowly bend your elbows and bring your hands towards your shoulders, keeping your upper arms still. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly extend your arms back out to the starting position. | Step:5 (dynamic variation) Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Leg Extension Declined
instructions: Step:1 Attach the resistance band to a sturdy anchor point and secure it around your ankle. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keeping your core engaged and your upper body stable, extend your leg straight out in front of you. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly return your leg to the starting position. Focus on declined movement. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Cable Concentration Curl Tempo
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the floor and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with an underhand grip and rest your elbow against the inside of your thigh. Focus on tempo movement. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the cable handle towards your shoulder while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then inhale and slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Barbell Reverse Preacher Curl Inclined
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your chest against the pad and your arms extended straight down, holding a barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the barbell upward while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the barbell is at shoulder level. Perform with inclined intensity. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Reverse Grip Preacher Curl With Precision
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the leverage machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:3 Rest your upper arms on the preacher pad, ensuring your elbows are fully extended. Maintain precision form throughout. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the handles towards your shoulders. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the handles back to the starting position, fully extending your elbows. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Prone Incline Curl With Intensive
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your chest and stomach resting against it. | Step:3 Hold a barbell with an underhand grip, shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully, allowing the barbell to hang down towards the floor. | Step:5 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level. | Step:7 (intensive variation) Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:8 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Reverse Grip Curl Resistance
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps, bringing the barbell as close to your shoulders as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Focus on resistance movement.

name: Cable Side Bend Smooth
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the cable handle with one hand. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Slowly bend sideways at the waist, lowering the cable handle towards your knee. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. Focus on smooth movement. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side. | Step:6 Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Flexible Cable Triceps Pushdown (V-Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a v-bar attachment to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the v-bar with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Engage your triceps and exhale as you push the v-bar down until your arms are fully extended. Perform with flexible intensity. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your triceps. | Step:7 Inhale as you slowly return the v-bar to the starting position, maintaining control. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hold Style Dumbbell Alternating Seated Bicep Curl On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl one dumbbell while rotating your forearm until your palm is facing your shoulder. | Step:4 (hold variation) Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the curl with the other arm. | Step:6 Continue alternating curls for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Active Style Cable Pushdown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and a slight bend in your knees. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary. | Step:5 Exhale and push the bar down until your elbows are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then inhale and slowly return the bar to the starting position. Maintain active form throughout. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Intermediate Style Dumbbell Preacher Curl Over Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip, resting your elbow on the exercise ball. | Step:3 (intermediate variation) Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Prone Hammer Curl - Macro Variation
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing your body and arm fully extended. | Step:2 Keep your upper arm stationary and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder, contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms. Focus on macro movement.

name: Rough Cable Standing One Arm Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with your right hand, palm facing down, and position your arm so that it is fully extended and parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Keep your elbow stationary and close to your body. | Step:4 Slowly bend your elbow, lowering the cable handle towards the back of your head. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then extend your arm back to the starting position. Focus on rough movement. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and perform the exercise with your left arm.

name: Complete Style Ez Bar Lying Close Grip Triceps Extension Behind Head
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your head at the end of the bench. | Step:2 Hold the ez barbell with a close grip, palms facing up, and extend your arms straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the barbell behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. Maintain complete form throughout. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Hammer Curl With Traditional
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and rotate the palms of your hands until they are facing forward. | Step:3 This will be your starting position. | Step:4 Now, keeping the upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:6 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:7 Then, inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions. Focus on traditional movement.

name: Smith Machine Incline Tricep Extension - Straight Variation
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the smith machine so that the bar is at shoulder height. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully, lifting the bar off the rack and holding it directly above your chest. Focus on straight movement. | Step:5 Lower the bar slowly towards your forehead, keeping your elbows close to your head. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dynamic Style Barbell Lying Back Of The Head Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your head at the end of the bench. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart, and extend your arms straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the barbell behind your head by bending your elbows. Maintain dynamic form throughout. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Standing Triceps Extension (With Towel) With Horizontal
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a towel with both hands behind your head. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your ears and your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 (horizontal variation) Slowly extend your forearms upward, squeezing your triceps at the top. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the towel back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wall Style Dumbbell One Arm French Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing up and your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. Focus on wall movement. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight up towards the ceiling, keeping your elbow stationary. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Cross Body Hammer Curl V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps, bringing the dumbbells as close to your opposite shoulder as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Zottman Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher curl bench and hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip. | Step:2 Rest your upper arm on the preacher bench pad, allowing your arm to fully extend. | Step:3 Curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 At the top of the curl, rotate your wrist so that your palm faces up. | Step:5 Slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position, rotating your wrist back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Twist
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands in front of your chest, keeping your arms slightly bent. | Step:3 Engage your core and twist your torso to the right, pulling the cable across your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, feeling the contraction in your abs and obliques. | Step:5 Slowly return to the starting position, resisting the cable's pull. | Step:6 Repeat the movement to the left side. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and rotate the palms of your hands until they are facing forward. | Step:3 This will be your starting position. | Step:4 Now, keeping the upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:6 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:7 Then, inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight up overhead. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your upper arms close to your ears. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then straighten your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Place your feet flat on the ground and let your arms hang straight down with your palms facing your body. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, shrug your shoulders up towards your ears as high as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contraction for a moment, then slowly lower your shoulders back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Over Bench Neutral Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing up. | Step:2 Rest your forearms on the bench, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Bar Standing French Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the ez barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Raise the barbell above your head, fully extending your arms. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms close to your head, slowly lower the barbell behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl (With Arm Blaster)
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the floor and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with an underhand grip and rest your elbow against the inside of your thigh. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the cable handle towards your shoulder while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then inhale and slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Barbell Sitted Alternate Leg Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and hold a barbell across your thighs. | Step:2 Keeping your legs straight, lift one leg up as high as possible while keeping the other leg on the ground. | Step:3 Lower the raised leg back down and repeat with the other leg. | Step:4 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Alternating Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the band with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your sides and slowly curl one arm up towards your shoulder, squeezing your biceps at the top. | Step:3 Lower the arm back down to the starting position and repeat with the other arm. | Step:4 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez-Bar Biceps Curl (With Arm Blaster)
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the ez barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Place your upper arms against the arm blaster, keeping them stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Keeping your elbows close to your body, exhale and curl the barbell up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Hammer Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with a dumbbell in one hand and your upper arm resting on the pad. | Step:2 Hold the dumbbell with a neutral grip (palms facing your body). | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Incline Fly
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Lie back on the bench and press the dumbbells up to the starting position, directly above your chest. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hyght Dumbbell Fly
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight up over your chest, with a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:3 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then reverse the movement and bring the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Raise your heels off the ground as high as possible, using your calves. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and exhale as you curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the bar until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale as you slowly begin to lower the bar back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Lying Two-One Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to fit your body and sit on it with your back against the backrest. | Step:2 Place your legs on the lever pad, just above your ankles. | Step:3 Grasp the handles on the sides of the machine for support. | Step:4 Keeping your upper body still, exhale and curl your legs up towards your glutes. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower your legs back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher curl bench with your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip, resting your upper arm against the preacher pad. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Seated Reverse Grip One Arm Overhead Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with an underhand grip and extend your arm straight up overhead. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbow, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arm back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Seated Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso and arms extended down. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your elbows close to your torso. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the dumbbell in your right hand towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Pause for a brief moment, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the movement with your left arm. | Step:7 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Bar Seated Close Grip Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold an EZ barbell with an underhand grip. | Step:2 Rest your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:3 Curl the barbell up towards your shoulder while keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Single Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in one hand and your arm fully extended above your chest. | Step:2 Lower the dumbbell in a controlled manner towards your forehead, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:3 Pause briefly at the bottom of the movement, then extend your arm back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Sled 45 Calf Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Place your feet on the sled platform with your toes pointing forward. | Step:3 Push the sled platform away from you by extending your ankles and calves. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the sled platform back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in your right hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Bring your right elbow up to your side, keeping it bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:4 Extend your right arm straight back, squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement. | Step:5 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Ez Barbell Seated Curls
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold the ez barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Rest your upper arms on your thighs, allowing the ez barbell to hang down in front of you. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the ez barbell upwards towards your shoulders. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the ez barbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbells Seated Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in both hands with an overhand grip, and raise it above your head. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your upper arms close to your ears. | Step:4 Extend your arms and raise the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and lean forward from your hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Bring your upper arms close to your sides and keep your elbows bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:4 Extend your arms straight back, squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grasp the cable attachment with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:3 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary. | Step:4 Exhale and curl the cable attachment towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the cable attachment back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Supine Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight up towards the ceiling. | Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your elbows close to your ears. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Barbell Spider Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the ez barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Rest your upper arms on a preacher bench or stability ball, allowing your elbows to hang down. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the barbell up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbell overhead, keeping your arm straight. | Step:3 Bend your elbow and lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Extend your arm back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Olympic Barbell Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding the barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Raise the barbell above your head, fully extending your arms. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms close to your head, slowly lower the barbell behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Prone Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing down. | Step:2 Extend your arm fully, letting it hang straight down towards the floor. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Barbell Pin Presses
instructions: Step:1 Set up a barbell on a power rack at chest height. | Step:2 Stand facing the barbell and position yourself underneath it, with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grip the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest, with your arms fully extended. | Step:5 Lower the barbell down towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in close to your body. | Step:6 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:7 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Overhead Triceps Extension (Rope Attachment)
