instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a cable machine at a high position. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with both hands, palms facing each other, and bring your hands above your head. | Step:4 Keep your upper arms close to your head and your elbows pointing forward. | Step:5 Slowly lower the rope behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Lying Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your chest against the pad and your arms extended over the edge, holding a barbell with an underhand grip. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the bar until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Tricep Kickback With Stork Stance
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in your right hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Bring your right elbow up to your side, keeping it bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:4 Extend your right arm straight back, squeezing your triceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Lever Seated Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to fit your body and sit on it with your back against the backrest. | Step:2 Place your lower legs under the padded lever, just above your ankles. | Step:3 Grasp the handles on the sides of the machine for support. | Step:4 Keeping your upper legs stationary, exhale and curl your legs up as far as possible. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your hamstrings. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the lever back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grasp the cable handles with an overhand grip and let your arms hang down in front of you. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, shrug your shoulders up towards your ears. | Step:4 Hold the contraction for a moment, then slowly lower your shoulders back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Floor Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Place a barbell on the floor in front of you. | Step:2 Stand with the balls of your feet on the edge of the barbell, with your heels hanging off. | Step:3 Hold onto a stable object for balance if needed. | Step:4 Raise your heels as high as possible, using your calves to lift your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Extension (Across Face)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your head at the end of the bench. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight up above your chest, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the dumbbell in an arc behind your head until your forearms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then contract your triceps to bring the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Inner Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Rest your upper arms on the bench, allowing your elbows to hang down and your palms to face forward. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Reverse Spider Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing down and arm fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arm stationary, curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder by flexing your elbow. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Pulldown Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary. | Step:5 Exhale and slowly curl the bar down towards your thighs, keeping your wrists straight. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly return the bar to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Side Bend
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the cable handle with one hand. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Slowly bend sideways at the waist, lowering the cable handle towards your knee. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side. | Step:6 Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Reverse Grip Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the leverage machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:3 Rest your upper arms on the preacher pad, ensuring your elbows are fully extended. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the handles towards your shoulders. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the handles back to the starting position, fully extending your elbows. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Standing Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing forward and arm fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the weight upward while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable One Arm Reverse Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the pulley is at the lowest position. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handle with an underhand grip and position your upper arm against the preacher bench pad. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Slowly curl your forearm towards your bicep, keeping your upper arm stationary against the pad. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your bicep. | Step:7 Slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:9 Switch arms and repeat the exercise.

name: Cable Reverse-Grip Pushdown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Using your triceps, push the bar down until your arms are fully extended and your triceps are contracted. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Seated Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a chair or bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the resistance band with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and arms extended down by your sides. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the resistance band up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the resistance band back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing up. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your elbows close to your torso. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Bench Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight up above your head. | Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your elbows close to your ears. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Reverse Grip One Arm Overhead Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing away from the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with an underhand grip and extend your arm overhead, keeping your elbow close to your head. | Step:3 Keep your upper arm stationary and slowly lower the cable handle behind your head by bending your elbow. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then extend your arm back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Standing Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Spider Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing One Arm Curl (Over Incline Bench)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing forward. | Step:2 Place your other hand on an incline bench for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Lever Hammer Grip Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the leverage machine. | Step:2 Place your upper arms on the preacher pad, ensuring your chest is pressed against it. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with a hammer grip (palms facing each other). | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the handles towards your shoulders. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the handles back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Calf Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the leverage machine so that your shoulders are aligned with the lever pad. | Step:2 Place your toes on the lever pad, with your heels hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or side supports for stability. | Step:4 Push the lever pad down by extending your ankles, contracting your calf muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement. | Step:6 Slowly return to the starting position by allowing your heels to rise back up. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Biceps Curl (With Arm Blaster)
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Place the arm blaster on your upper arms, ensuring a secure fit. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl one dumbbell up towards your shoulder while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat the movement with the opposite arm. | Step:8 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Pushdown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and a slight bend in your knees. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary. | Step:5 Exhale and push the bar down until your elbows are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then inhale and slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the leverage machine. | Step:2 Place your upper arms on the pad and grip the handles with an underhand grip. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your elbows positioned on the pad. | Step:4 Exhale and curl your forearms towards your upper arms, contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the handles back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl Reverse
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing down and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Two Arm Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Slowly lie back on the bench, keeping the dumbbells close to your chest. | Step:3 Once you are fully lying down, extend your arms straight up towards the ceiling, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Alternating Seated Bicep Curl On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl one dumbbell while rotating your forearm until your palm is facing your shoulder. | Step:4 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the curl with the other arm. | Step:6 Continue alternating curls for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Barbell Close Grip Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher curl bench and place your upper arms on the pad, gripping the ez barbell with an underhand grip. | Step:2 Rest your triceps on the pad and fully extend your arms, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Slowly curl the barbell towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Lower the barbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward, and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Over Bench One Arm Neutral Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in one hand and your arm extended over the bench, palm facing up. | Step:2 Keep your upper arm stationary and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder, keeping your wrist in a neutral position. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Band Side Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the band with both hands, palms facing down. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out to the sides, keeping them parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Slowly bend your elbows and bring your hands towards your shoulders, keeping your upper arms still. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly extend your arms back out to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Side Bend
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand, letting it hang down by your side. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, slowly bend sideways at the waist towards the opposite side of the dumbbell, lowering the weight as far as you comfortably can. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and repeat.

name: Cable One Arm Tricep Pushdown
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with a straight bar attachment at chest height. | Step:2 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip and step back to create tension in the cable. | Step:3 Position your feet shoulder-width apart and slightly bend your knees. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Start with your arm fully extended and perpendicular to the floor. | Step:6 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and push the bar down until your arm is fully extended. | Step:7 Pause for a moment, then inhale and slowly return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Seated Inner Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing up. | Step:2 Rest your upper arms on your thighs, allowing the dumbbells to hang down. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Biceps Curl To Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward and arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your elbows close to your sides, curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Once your forearms are vertical, rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing forward. | Step:5 Press the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position by reversing the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Hammer Curls (With Arm Blaster)
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and rotate the palms of your hands until they are facing forward. | Step:3 This will be your starting position. | Step:4 Now, while holding your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:6 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:7 Then, inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.

name: Lever Preacher Curl V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your upper arms resting on the pad and your chest against the support. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an underhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your upper arms stationary and exhale as you curl the handles towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale as you slowly lower the handles back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Barbell Seated Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the ez barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Raise the barbell overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, lower the barbell behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then raise the barbell back to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Reverse Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your chest against the pad and your arm extended over the edge of the bench, holding a dumbbell with an underhand grip. | Step:2 Lower the dumbbell slowly until your arm is fully extended. | Step:3 Curl the dumbbell back up towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Peacher Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and rotate the palms of your hands until they are facing forward. | Step:3 This will be your starting position. | Step:4 Now, keeping the upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:6 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:7 Then, inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.

name: Cable Lying Triceps Extension V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Lie down on a flat bench facing up, with your head towards the cable machine. | Step:3 Grasp the rope handle with both hands, palms facing each other, and extend your arms straight up over your chest. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the rope handle towards your forehead by bending your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope Lying On Floor Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a cable machine and set it to the lowest position. | Step:2 Lie on the floor facing up, with your head towards the cable machine. | Step:3 Hold the rope with both hands, palms facing each other, and extend your arms straight up towards the ceiling. | Step:4 Keep your upper arms stationary and slowly lower the rope towards your forehead, bending your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Alternate Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with your right hand and bring your arm up so that your upper arm is parallel to the ground and your elbow is bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Keep your upper arm stationary and extend your forearm backward, fully straightening your arm. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with your left arm. | Step:6 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope High Pulley Overhead Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a high pulley and adjust the weight accordingly. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the pulley machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with both hands, palms facing down, and bring your hands above your head. | Step:4 Keep your upper arms close to your head and perpendicular to the floor. | Step:5 Slowly lower the rope behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Revers Grip Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing up. | Step:2 Rest your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Barbell Standing Close Grip Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an underhand grip, hands close together. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary throughout the movement. | Step:3 Exhale as you curl the weights while contracting your biceps. Continue to raise the bar until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale as you slowly begin to bring the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Triceps Pushdown (V-Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a v-bar attachment to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the v-bar with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Engage your triceps and exhale as you push the v-bar down until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your triceps. | Step:7 Inhale as you slowly return the v-bar to the starting position, maintaining control. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Lying Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to fit your body and select the desired weight. | Step:2 Lie face down on the machine with your legs straight and your heels against the padded lever. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or the sides of the machine for stability. | Step:4 Keeping your upper body stationary, exhale and curl your legs up as far as possible without lifting your hips off the pad. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your hamstrings. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the lever back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Reverse Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the band with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and wrap it around your fingers. | Step:3 Rest your forearms on your thighs, with your wrists hanging off the edge. | Step:4 Slowly curl your wrists upward, squeezing your forearms. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your wrists back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with your right hand and step back to create tension in the cable. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Keep your upper arm close to your body and your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:5 Extend your forearm backward, straightening your arm fully. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Ez-Barbell Standing Wide Grip Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the ez barbell with an underhand grip, hands wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary throughout the movement. | Step:3 Curl the barbell up towards your shoulders by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor and a barbell resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Place the balls of your feet on a raised platform, such as a block or step. | Step:3 Lower your heels as far as possible, feeling a stretch in your calves. | Step:4 Raise your heels as high as possible, contracting your calves. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Zottman Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and rotate your palms to face forward. | Step:3 Curl the dumbbells up to your shoulders while keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:4 At the top of the movement, rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing away from your body. | Step:5 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, rotating your palms back to facing your body. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Supinated Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your back and head supported, and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip, and extend your arm straight up above your shoulder. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbow. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then extend your arm back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Kneeling Bicep Curl Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the floor with an exercise ball in front of you. | Step:2 Place your elbows on top of the exercise ball, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing up. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbells while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bicep Curl With Stork Stance
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Extend one leg behind you, balancing on the toes of that foot. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Seated Alternate Hammer Curl On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl one dumbbell up towards your shoulder while keeping your palm facing your body. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat the movement with the opposite arm. | Step:8 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Seated Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other). | Step:3 Rest your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Lever Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and keep your elbows close to your sides. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the handles upward, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the handles back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight up over your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells down towards your forehead, bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your elbows close to your sides, exhale and curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:4 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Biceps Curl (With Arm Blaster)
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Place your upper arms against the arm blaster, keeping your elbows close to your torso. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Lying Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your head at the end of the bench. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart, and extend your arms straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the barbell towards your forehead by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Arm Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Bend your torso forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight back, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Ez Bar Lying Close Grip Triceps Extension Behind Head
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your head at the end of the bench. | Step:2 Hold the ez barbell with a close grip, palms facing up, and extend your arms straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the barbell behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Pronate-Grip Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands, palms facing down, and extend your arms straight up overhead. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms close to your head and elbows pointing forward, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Femoral
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and a dumbbell resting on your lower abdomen. | Step:2 Bend your knees and bring the dumbbell towards your glutes, keeping your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Prone Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing your body and arm fully extended. | Step:2 Keep your upper arm stationary and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder, contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Ez Barbell Spider Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the ez barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Rest your upper arms on a preacher bench or stability ball, allowing your elbows to hang down. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the barbell up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Cross Body Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps, bringing the dumbbells across your body towards your opposite shoulder. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your legs spread apart and a dumbbell in one hand, resting your elbow on the inside of your thigh. | Step:2 Fully extend your arm and hold the dumbbell with an underhand grip. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the weight up towards your shoulder while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Squatting Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable handle to the lowest setting on a cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the cable handle with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and arms fully extended. | Step:4 Lower your body into a squat position, keeping your back straight and knees behind your toes. | Step:5 As you squat down, curl the cable handle towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the curl, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Close-Grip Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor and hold a barbell with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Rest your upper arms against your inner thighs, just above your knees, and let the barbell hang down in front of you. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the barbell up towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause, then inhale and slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope One Arm Hammer Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope handle with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:4 Position your upper arm against the preacher bench pad, keeping your elbow slightly bent. | Step:5 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:6 Slowly curl the rope handle towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:7 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the rope handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Lying Close-Grip Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Lie face up on a flat bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:5 Keeping your upper arms stationary, curl the bar towards your chest by contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Prone Incline Curl
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your chest and stomach resting against it. | Step:3 Hold a barbell with an underhand grip, shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully, allowing the barbell to hang down towards the floor. | Step:5 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level. | Step:7 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:8 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Hip Extension V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to fit your body and sit on it with your back against the backrest. | Step:2 Place your feet on the footrests and grip the handles for stability. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and hamstrings, then push against the footrests to extend your hips and raise your legs backward. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Tate Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, then rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing away from you. | Step:3 Press the dumbbells up until your arms are fully extended, then lower them back down to shoulder height. | Step:4 Rotate your wrists back to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grasp the cable handle with an underhand grip, palm facing up. | Step:3 Keep your elbow close to your side and slowly curl your forearm up towards your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your forearm back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher curl bench with your upper arms resting on the pad and your chest against it. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing up and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Overhead Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Raise the barbell overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms close to your head, slowly lower the barbell behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the barbell back to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Prone Incline Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the bench to a 45-degree incline. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Allow your arms to hang straight down towards the floor, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:6 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope Incline Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a high pulley and adjust the incline bench to a comfortable angle. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the pulley with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip and extend your arms straight overhead. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your head and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Lower the rope behind your head by bending your elbows until your forearms touch your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell in one hand, palm facing up. | Step:2 Rest your opposite hand on your thigh for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the weight up towards your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the weight back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Reverse Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the preacher curl pad is at chest height. | Step:2 Sit on the preacher curl bench and place your upper arms on the pad, with your palms facing down and your elbows fully extended. | Step:3 Grab the cable handles with an underhand grip, shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the handles towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the handles back to the starting position, fully extending your elbows. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Machine Incline Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the smith machine so that the bar is at shoulder height. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully, lifting the bar off the rack and holding it directly above your chest. | Step:5 Lower the bar slowly towards your forehead, keeping your elbows close to your head. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Olympic Barbell Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold an Olympic barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Let the barbell hang at arm's length in front of your thighs, with your palms facing your body. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the barbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso and arms extended straight down. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Supine Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing up and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Hammer Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keep your upper arms stationary and exhale as you curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Rest the back of your upper arms against the preacher bench or an incline bench, with your elbows slightly bent. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Barbell Reverse Grip Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the ez barbell with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Rest your upper arms on the pad, allowing your forearms to hang down. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the barbell up towards your shoulders. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Barbell Decline Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your head lower than your feet and your feet secured. | Step:2 Hold the ez barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Extend your arms fully, keeping your elbows close to your head. | Step:4 Lower the barbell slowly towards your forehead, bending your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Lying Close-Grip Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your head at the end of the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, hands shoulder-width apart, palms facing up. | Step:3 Extend your arms fully, lifting the barbell above your chest. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the barbell towards your forehead by bending your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Wide Grip Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an underhand grip, hands wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your elbows close to your torso. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the barbell up towards your shoulders, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your chest against the pad and your arms extended straight down, holding a barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the barbell upward while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the barbell is at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Supine Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your back and head supported, and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing up and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing One Arm Curl Over Incline Bench
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Place your other hand on an incline bench for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Barbell Drag Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Let the barbell hang at arm's length in front of your thighs. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, curl the barbell up towards your chest by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Barbell Reverse Grip Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the ez barbell with an underhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Curl the barbell upwards by contracting your biceps, while exhaling. | Step:4 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the barbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Slowly begin to bring the barbell back to the starting position as you inhale. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your legs spread apart and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold one end of the band in your hand and step on the other end with your foot on the same side. | Step:3 Lean forward slightly and rest your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:4 With your palm facing up, slowly curl your hand towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hand back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, alternating arms.

name: Barbell Standing Reverse Grip Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps, bringing the barbell as close to your shoulders as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your elbows close to your torso. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Bring your upper arms close to your sides, with your elbows bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:4 Extend your arms straight back, squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Seated Bicep Curl On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing up and your arm fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Ez Barbell Close-Grip Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the ez barbell with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary throughout the movement. | Step:3 Curl the barbell up towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Kneeling Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to fit your body and select the desired weight. | Step:2 Kneel on the machine facing downwards, with your knees resting on the pad and your feet secured under the footpads. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or the sides of the machine for stability. | Step:4 Keeping your upper body stationary, exhale and curl your legs up towards your glutes by flexing your knees. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your hamstrings. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower your legs back to the starting position, fully extending your knees. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your head lower than your feet and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Extend your arms fully, keeping your elbows close to your head. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells slowly behind your head, bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Fly On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on an exercise ball and roll forward until your upper back is resting on the incline bench. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing each other and your arms extended above your chest. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Lying Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Lie face up on a flat bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:5 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the bar up towards your shoulders. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly lower the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Reverse Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Exhale and curl the bar up towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly lower the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Curl
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Rest your upper arms on the incline bench and let your elbows hang down, fully extending your arms. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Zottman Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing up and elbows resting on the pad. | Step:2 Curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, keeping your upper arms stationary and your palms facing up. | Step:3 At the top of the curl, rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing down. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position, rotating your wrists back to the starting position as you do so. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable High Pulley Overhead Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a high pulley and stand facing away from the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the rope with both hands and extend your arms overhead. | Step:3 Keep your elbows close to your head and your upper arms stationary. | Step:4 Slowly lower the rope behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inwards. | Step:2 Extend your arms fully overhead, keeping your elbows close to your head. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells behind your head by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbells back to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Inner Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grasp the cable handle with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:3 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary. | Step:4 Exhale and curl the cable handle towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Fly On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward and roll your body down until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell with your arm extended straight up over your chest, palm facing inwards. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell out to the side, keeping a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when your arm is parallel to the ground. | Step:6 Engage your chest muscles to bring the dumbbell back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Incline Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a low pulley position. | Step:2 Attach a straight bar to the cable. | Step:3 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip and extend your arms straight overhead. | Step:5 Lean forward slightly, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:6 Bend your elbows and lower the bar behind your head, keeping your upper arms close to your ears. | Step:7 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Close Grip Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Exhale and curl the bar up towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly lower the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Fly
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet secured and your head lower than your hips. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing each other and your arms extended above your chest. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Lying Back Of The Head Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your head at the end of the bench. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart, and extend your arms straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the barbell behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing One Arm Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing up. | Step:2 Place your free hand on your thigh for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Rope Incline Tricep Extension - Reverse Variation
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a high pulley and adjust the incline bench to a comfortable angle. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the pulley with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip and extend your arms straight overhead. | Step:4 (reverse variation) Keep your elbows close to your head and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Lower the rope behind your head by bending your elbows until your forearms touch your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.
